It allegedly took two “contaminated” bottles of Autumn Harvest Crackling Rosé to ruin the reputation of a Joburg liquor supplier, and now he’s suing Distell, the company that made the offending bottles, for R500,000. Fortunatus Ogbonna and his lawyer, Kingdom Onah, still can’t identify the “worm-like” object that was found inside the bottles, but the business owner said that because of them, he’s been the subject of xenophobic threats and a major loss in business. Read the full story on Times Select.